Meta des: Explore how to write an effective webinar follow up email with 13 real examples, smart segmentation, and tips to drive leads, clicks, and next steps.\
Let\'92s be real\'97hosting a webinar is only half the battle.\
The real magic happens 
\f1\i after
\f0\i0  the session, when you follow up.\
Whether your audience showed up live or meant to and just didn\'92t make it (we\'92ve all been there), your webinar follow-up email is where you reconnect, add value, and keep the momentum going.\
In this guide, we\'92re diving into real examples, key tips, and a few things to avoid so your follow-ups actually 
\f1\i do
\f0\i0  something.\
Ready? Let's go.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf0 Why webinar follow-up emails actually matter\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 You\'92ve hosted a compelling webinar. Great! Now what? A strong webinar follow up email keeps the momentum going, nudging webinar attendees toward the next step\'97whether that\'92s a demo, a download, or your next event.\
It's a crucial part of your webinar strategy and helps boost webinar ROI. Without it, all that great webinar content fades fast from attendees\'92 minds. The post webinar moment is where the real lead generation magic happens.\
Still working on your invite? Check out {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.digistorms.com/blog/webinar-emails"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 our guide to writing high-converting webinar emails with 13 real examples}} to get more signups before you follow up.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf0 Tailoring your message to your audience\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Not all webinar participants are the same. Your follow up message should reflect who showed up, who didn\'92t, and what they need next.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 For attendees\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 If someone attended your recent webinar, they\'92re already engaged\'97so your follow up email should reflect that. Thank them for attending, remind them of the key takeaways, and give them access to the webinar recording link or additional resources.\
You might also encourage recipients to join future webinars or share the webinar replay with a colleague. This is your chance to nurture leads with smart post webinar communication that feels like a natural next step.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 For no-shows\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Webinar registrants who missed the session are still valuable leads. They signed up, which means the webinar topic caught their attention. Your follow up email for non-attendees should focus on value without guilt.\
Share the webinar recording, bonus materials, or a quick summary of what they missed. Add a webinar date for the next event or offer a follow up template that makes their life easier. This keeps your webinar email sequence inclusive and welcoming.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs36 \cf0 What a follow-up should always include\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 No matter who you\'92re emailing, there are a few must-haves that every post webinar email needs to keep attendees engaged and moving forward.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 A short recap\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Summarize the session with 2\'963 sentences that highlight the most valuable insights. This helps attendees remember why the session was worth their time\'97and gives no-shows a reason to dive into the replay.\
Keep it relevant to the original webinar title and target audience. A recap helps frame any future events, especially if you\'92re building a full webinar {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.digistorms.com/blog/lifecycle-email-marketing"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 email sequence}} around an ongoing webinar marketing strategy.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 The recording\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Include a clear, friendly webinar recording link\'97ideally above the fold. Whether someone attended or not, this is the most requested part of any follow up. Make it obvious, easy to access, and mention how long the recording will be available.\
Webinar platforms often give you tools to track who clicked, helping you segment your follow up process more effectively for nurturing leads.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf0 A clear CTA tailored to each segment\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 One CTA to rule them all? Not quite. The best follow up {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.digistorms.com/blog/email-marketing-for-saas"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 email templates}} include specific next steps for different segments. Leads might get a \'93start a trial\'94 link, while current customers get bonus materials or an upgrade incentive.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li800\fi-800\ri800\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \uc0\u55357 \u56481  Segmenting based on webinar attendance or account status helps you guide webinar participants deeper into the sales funnel\'97without overwhelming them. This is where webinar follow ups really drive conversions.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
